 type-of-imaginary-part) in general.

If you want a new random state on each invocation, you can arrange
 for that by using &init-function;: 
&sh-prompt; clisp -norc &opt-x; '(&savemem; "foo" :init-function (&lambda-m; () (&setq; &random-state-var; (&make-random-state; &t;))))'
&sh-prompt; clisp -norc &opt-M; foo.mem &opt-x; '(&random; 1s0)'
 or by placing (&setq; &random-state-var;
  (&make-random-state; &t;)) into your &RC-file;.

