This is the list of objects whose external representation cannot be meaningfully read in:
Unreadable objects
formatmeaning
#<&type-r; ...> all &structure-object-t;s lacking a keyword constructor
#<ARRAY &type-r; &dimensions-r;> all &array-t;s except &string-t;s, if &print-array-var; is &nil;
#<SYSTEM-FUNCTION &name-r;> built-in function written in &c-lang;
#<ADD-ON-SYSTEM-FUNCTION &name-r;> &module; function written in &c-lang;
#<SPECIAL-OPERATOR &name-r;> special operator handler
#<COMPILED-CLOSURE &name-r;> compiled function, if &pr-closure; is &nil;
#<CLOSURE &name-r; ...> interpreted function
#<FRAME-POINTER #x...> pointer to a stack frame
#<DISABLED POINTER> frame pointer which has become invalid on exit from the corresponding █ or &tagbody;
#<...STREAM...> &stream-t;
#<PACKAGE &name-r;> &package-t;
#<HASH-TABLE #x...> &hash-table-t;, if &print-array-var; is &nil;
#<READTABLE #x...> &readtable-t;
#<SYMBOL-MACRO &form-r;> &symbol-macro; handler
#<MACRO &func-r;> macro expander (defined by &defmacro; and friends)
#<&foreign-pointer-t; #x...> foreign pointer (&unix-w32-only;)
#<&foreign-address-t; #x...> foreign address (&unix-w32-only;)
#<&foreign-variable-t; &name-r; #x...> foreign variable (&unix-w32-only;)
#<&foreign-function-t; &name-r; #x...> foreign function (&unix-w32-only;)
#<UNBOUND> value of an unbound symbol, an unsupplied optional or keyword argument
#<SPECIAL REFERENCE> environment marker for variables declared &special-dec;
#<DOT> internal &read; result for .
#<END OF FILE> internal &read; result, when the &eos; is reached
#<READ-LABEL ...> intermediate &read; result for &sharp-sharp;
#<ADDRESS #x...> machine address, should not occur
#<SYSTEM-POINTER #x...> should not occur

